My experience here was a total mess. Where do I begin? When some of my party first got there, the staff started off amazing. I remember thinking, this is going to be great. We opted to wait until everyone got there to order. Once our full party arrived we were seated in a more accommodating section. The waitress who was obviously new and had never waited on a large party or had little exprerience served our table. She took only 3 people's order. She came back maybe 10 minutes later and we had to tell her to take our orders. There were about 10 of us. A few minutes later someone(later identified as the mgr) brought a fried egg to the table. We were all looking like where is the food that goes with it? She said oh it was placed seperately. Can you take it back until the rest of the food is ready? Of course the 3 people who ordered first got their plates with no problem and rather quickly. The other 7 however waited different amounts of time. Mind you there was not many people in the restaurant at the time. Maybe 2 other families, it was still early. Three of us got the same meal but waited at least 15 apart to receive our plates. They brought out parts of several meals and we had to ask for it was a side condiment or something. Not acceptable. I have never been to a restaurant that brought the meals out seperately. Meals should be eaten together right? My pancakes were soft and moist but were not fresh. They were either day before or hours before. I had to use a spoon because they were falling apart. They appeared to be those pancakes that you reheat(that was leftover from breakfast and in between dinner). The birthday girl who by the way had shrimp and grits didn't get her food until EVERYONE and I do mean EVERYONE was finishing up. She only took a few bites and a to go box. She was just ready to go at this point. We asked begore hand if the bills could be seperate which the waitress said yes. Come time to pay the bill, that wasn't the case. We found out that it would only take 3 cards(for 10 people?). So we're sitting here trying to figure out how we were going to do this. The manager finally came out. Although Im not sure if she was ever called or notified. The waitress said, she doesn't come out any way. What do you mean? Huh? When she got to the table, she reeked of cigarette smoke. Im not sure of the ettiquette or sanitation practices but reeking of cigarettes may be a common sense thing. I would have washed my hands and tried to cover up the smell at least. So upon trying to figure out why she hadn't made it to the table with major problems, she discloses that she was on the phone with the manager. I expressed my disappointment for the service and the fact that it took so long for her to come out. In my opinion, the fact that you have a very upset table full of customers that will not be back, trumps a manger's call. I personally would have said Boss I have a table of unhappy customers, is it ok to table this discussion for about 15 to 20 minutes? They made excuse after excuse, dis not stand nor work as a team and called out the peopl who were to blame for every problem we had instead of just quietly and apologetically correcting it. My whole party vowed to never come back. Service was horrible, management was horrible which is sad because the food actually wasn't too bad. I forgot to mention we had to keep reminding the staff that we hadn't received certain orders. We spent more time fussing over our food than actually enjoying it.
